PT Sans family was developed as a part of the project "Public Types of
Russian Federation". The fonts of this project have an open user license
and can be freely distributed. The main aim of the project is to allow
the peoples of Russia to read and write in their native languages.

PT Sans is based on Russian sans serif types.
The family consists of 8 styles: 4 basic styles; 2 caption styles for
small sizes and 2 narrow styles for economic setting.
